WEBVTT

00:02.336 --> 00:03.404
Letty: So you were going
to kill someone?

00:03.437 --> 00:04.672
Javier: Yes.
And it was a trap.

00:04.705 --> 00:06.574
He was another hit man
there to kill me.

00:06.607 --> 00:08.509
Who wants you dead?
I don't know.

00:08.542 --> 00:10.244
We need enough money.

00:10.278 --> 00:11.412
Can't you just steal some?

00:11.445 --> 00:13.147
I'm not doing
those things anymore.

00:13.181 --> 00:14.648
I want a clean start.

00:14.682 --> 00:18.052
I'm sorry. We have
no room for your son.

00:18.086 --> 00:19.520
I'm Carin with a "C."

00:19.553 --> 00:22.256
You can't just invite
strangers into our house.

00:22.290 --> 00:23.424
Apple wants to help.

00:23.457 --> 00:25.093
She wants me to go
to her school.

00:25.126 --> 00:27.328
Diversity
is my campaign platform.

00:27.361 --> 00:29.597
I want to go to
a real school with other kids.

00:29.630 --> 00:31.532
We are gonna get him
into Apple's school.

00:31.565 --> 00:33.534
Thanks.
[ Glasses clink ]

00:45.146 --> 00:47.215
Letty:
Is she going after Javier?

00:47.248 --> 00:49.317
Yes, she is.

00:56.124 --> 00:59.026
[ Birds calling ]

00:59.059 --> 01:03.931
[ Cellphone alarm rings ]

01:05.099 --> 01:06.834
[ Sighs softly ]

01:18.946 --> 01:20.481
Hey.

01:20.514 --> 01:21.582
Hey.

01:23.917 --> 01:26.420
When did you get up?

01:26.454 --> 01:29.523
I'm not sure.

01:30.824 --> 01:32.926
[ Birds chirping ]

01:48.176 --> 01:49.843
I'm sorry.

01:49.877 --> 01:52.980
That I made you take
the body to Silk.

01:54.114 --> 01:56.284
It was good that you did.

01:56.317 --> 01:59.853
No, it wasn't.

01:59.887 --> 02:03.757
He would still be dead.
And I wouldn't know.

02:03.791 --> 02:06.794
But it wouldn't have been you
who had to find him.

02:13.133 --> 02:15.203
What time is it?

02:15.236 --> 02:18.539
I don't know.

02:18.572 --> 02:20.140
What time did you
set your alarm for?

02:20.174 --> 02:21.209
[ Inhales sharply ]

02:21.242 --> 02:23.311
8:02.

02:23.344 --> 02:25.713
Then it's 8:02.

02:25.746 --> 02:29.983
It's -- I mean,
it's probably 8:03 by now.

02:30.017 --> 02:31.419
Or four.

02:35.256 --> 02:36.457
You should get ready.

02:36.490 --> 02:38.359
You will be late.

02:44.064 --> 02:46.500
[ School bell rings ]

02:46.534 --> 02:48.569
And I'm hearing you,
ma'am,

02:48.602 --> 02:51.405
but we have absolutely
no more space.

02:51.439 --> 02:53.407
Ma'am, I'm hanging up
the phone now.

02:53.441 --> 02:55.376
[ Beep, click ]

02:55.409 --> 02:56.910
How can I help you?

02:56.944 --> 02:59.380
I'm here to schedule
my son's interview.

02:59.413 --> 03:01.081
Oh! Is that Michael?

03:01.114 --> 03:03.150
Are you Lindsey?
Friends with Carin Jeffrey?

03:03.183 --> 03:04.385
Yeah, that's us.

03:04.418 --> 03:06.254
Great.
Do you have your paperwork?

03:06.287 --> 03:09.156
I do.
Here you go.

03:09.189 --> 03:10.624
Okay.

03:11.959 --> 03:16.364
Didn't you just fill this
all out perfectly.

03:16.397 --> 03:17.998
Oh.

03:18.031 --> 03:19.867
You get an A-plus.

03:19.900 --> 03:21.101
That's a first.

03:21.134 --> 03:24.538
Okay, let's see...we can
schedule Michael's interview

03:24.572 --> 03:27.107
with the headmaster
for Monday at 2:00.

03:27.140 --> 03:28.208
Does that work?

03:28.242 --> 03:31.279
Monday at 2:00.
Great.

03:31.312 --> 03:35.015
Now, if the interview goes well
and he gets in...

03:35.048 --> 03:37.685
[ School bell rings ]
...we will need

03:37.718 --> 03:39.787
this in a cashier's check

03:39.820 --> 03:40.954
the same day,

03:40.988 --> 03:43.557
so just be sure
to bring that with you.

03:43.591 --> 03:45.793
I have to bring in
this much on Monday?

03:45.826 --> 03:47.361
Yeah.
Cashier's check.

03:47.395 --> 03:50.298
-It's Friday.
-I know.

03:50.331 --> 03:52.300
Cashier's checks
are a bitch.

03:52.333 --> 03:55.903
Right.
So it has to be Monday?

03:55.936 --> 03:58.406
If you want him to start
after the holiday break --

03:58.439 --> 04:01.275
break starts Tuesday.

04:01.309 --> 04:03.944
Understood. Great.

04:03.977 --> 04:05.413
Monday at 2:00.

04:05.446 --> 04:06.814
Thank you, Paul.

04:06.847 --> 04:08.215
Bye, Lindsey.

04:08.248 --> 04:10.984
Bye, Michael!
Monday at 2:00.

04:12.420 --> 04:14.322
20 grand.
Letty: I know.

04:14.355 --> 04:15.489
For school.

04:15.523 --> 04:17.558
I know --
for one semester.

04:17.591 --> 04:21.429
Do they have a pool?
What?

04:21.462 --> 04:22.996
Why is it so expensive?

04:23.030 --> 04:26.099
A pool would make it okay
to be that expensive?

04:26.133 --> 04:27.335
I don't know. Maybe.

04:27.368 --> 04:29.770
No, there's no pool.

04:29.803 --> 04:32.172
And you didn't know this,
that it was this much?

04:32.205 --> 04:33.407
I -- no.

04:33.441 --> 04:35.676
I-I thought we could
pay it monthly.

04:35.709 --> 04:37.010
What do you want to do?

04:37.044 --> 04:39.480
I'm figuring it out.
Don't worry about it.

04:39.513 --> 04:41.749
I'll have the money
by Sunday night.

04:41.782 --> 04:43.517
No.

04:43.551 --> 04:44.918
No what?

04:44.952 --> 04:46.820
No, you're not stealing
20 grand

04:46.854 --> 04:50.491
from wherever you're
planning on stealing
20 grand from on Sunday.

04:50.524 --> 04:52.092
If you get caught,
you go to prison again.

04:52.125 --> 04:53.327
You'll lose Jacob forever.

04:53.361 --> 04:54.795
I'll also
lose him forever

04:54.828 --> 04:56.830
if he doesn't
start school somewhere.

04:56.864 --> 04:58.866
I'm not gonna get caught.

04:58.899 --> 05:02.503
How do you even
drink that shit?

05:05.973 --> 05:08.542
* Hard time forgiving

05:08.576 --> 05:11.379
* Even harder forgetting

05:11.412 --> 05:13.547
* Before you do something

05:13.581 --> 05:16.149
* You might regret, friend

05:16.183 --> 05:18.786
* Bricks are caving in

05:18.819 --> 05:20.954
* Oh, how sweet this sin

05:20.988 --> 05:23.791
* I left you the keys

05:23.824 --> 05:25.959
* You won't let me in

05:25.993 --> 05:28.562
* Hard time forgiving

05:28.596 --> 05:31.331
* Even harder forgetting

05:31.365 --> 05:33.567
* Before you do something

05:33.601 --> 05:37.170
* You might regret, friend

05:39.607 --> 05:42.309
[ Indistinct talking ]

05:42.342 --> 05:52.753
**

05:52.786 --> 05:57.190
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

07:19.172 --> 07:21.509
* Oh, oh-oh
* Oh, oh-oh

07:21.542 --> 07:24.244
* Oh, oh

07:24.277 --> 07:28.315
* I think it's time
that I take what's mine *

07:28.348 --> 07:29.917
* Mmm, mmm

07:29.950 --> 07:31.752
Letty:
What's going on?

07:31.785 --> 07:34.488
* Feel a change in that time

07:34.522 --> 07:36.423
What is this?

07:36.456 --> 07:38.759
What is happening?
* Never been to the wild side

07:38.792 --> 07:40.661
* Mmm
[ Scoffs ]

07:40.694 --> 07:42.963
Um, why is there a harmonica
in my house?

07:42.996 --> 07:44.464
This is not your house.

07:44.498 --> 07:46.299
We are renting this house.

07:46.333 --> 07:47.300
Who cares?

07:47.334 --> 07:48.435
What if Jacob sees this

07:48.468 --> 07:50.638
and wants to play
the stupid harmonica.

07:50.671 --> 07:52.272
What are we
gonna do then?

07:52.305 --> 07:54.542
He won't see it.
I'm taking it camping.

07:54.575 --> 07:55.709
Camping?

07:55.743 --> 07:57.711
Mm-hmm.
Gross.

07:57.745 --> 07:59.179
I'm not going camping
with you.

07:59.212 --> 08:01.148
I know.
You're not invited.

08:01.181 --> 08:03.050
So who are you
going camping with?

08:03.083 --> 08:04.685
You don't have
any friends.

08:04.718 --> 08:05.953
[ Sighs ]

08:05.986 --> 08:08.188
* Loaded shotgun

08:08.221 --> 08:11.024
Wh-- You don't have to
go alone.

08:11.058 --> 08:12.660
Why don't you take Jacob?

08:12.693 --> 08:14.394
He probably loves that shit.

08:14.427 --> 08:15.829
I am not taking Jacob.

08:15.863 --> 08:17.364
Where are you going?

08:17.397 --> 08:18.566
It doesn't matter.

08:18.599 --> 08:21.234
What if there's
an emergency?

08:21.268 --> 08:23.403
Tybee State Park.

08:23.436 --> 08:27.174
So, what, you're just gonna be
in the woods all alone?

08:27.207 --> 08:28.208
Take Jacob.

08:28.241 --> 08:29.309
I am not taking Jacob.

08:29.342 --> 08:30.544
Why not?

08:30.578 --> 08:34.147
Because the last time I took
a child camping, he died.

08:34.181 --> 08:37.050
You want to know why
I'm going camping?

08:37.084 --> 08:40.420
Because it is the anniversary
of Little Santino's death.

08:40.453 --> 08:43.223
Every year at this time
I take a night --

08:43.256 --> 08:45.759
I sit in the woods
and I think about

08:45.793 --> 08:48.929
all the things my baby brother
could have become,

08:48.962 --> 08:51.198
all the things
he never got to be.

08:51.231 --> 08:54.768
And I light a fire
for him.

08:54.802 --> 08:57.204
And I do that alone,
by myself.

08:57.237 --> 09:01.341
And meeting you
doesn't change that, okay?

09:01.374 --> 09:02.910
Okay.

09:02.943 --> 09:04.778
I'll be back tomorrow.

09:04.812 --> 09:09.783
**

09:09.817 --> 09:12.552
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

09:12.586 --> 09:22.095
**

09:22.129 --> 09:25.498
How long did you know him
before he told you what he did?

09:28.401 --> 09:32.072
I don't know...
um, a couple of months?

09:32.105 --> 09:34.574
But you're still with him.

09:34.608 --> 09:37.244
He -- he said
he would stop.

09:37.277 --> 09:41.448
Did he? Did he stop?

09:41.481 --> 09:42.883
He said he did.

09:42.916 --> 09:46.019
He has a job
as a line cook.

09:49.322 --> 09:51.558
How are the girls?

09:51.591 --> 09:54.728
Confused.

09:54.762 --> 09:55.929
Their father is dead.

09:55.963 --> 09:57.731
They can't see
their uncle.

09:57.765 --> 10:00.000
I can't tell them
the truth.

10:00.033 --> 10:02.002
Javier misses them.

10:02.035 --> 10:05.405
And they miss him, but --
So let's end this.

10:05.438 --> 10:09.076
Let them have him
when they need him most.

10:09.109 --> 10:11.144
He's camping for Santino.

10:11.178 --> 10:12.680
He'll be back tomorrow.

10:12.713 --> 10:15.148
Just let him see them.

10:15.182 --> 10:16.449
Where is he?

10:16.483 --> 10:20.053
His camping-for-Santino thing
he does every year.

10:22.956 --> 10:25.859
On the anniversary
of...you know.

10:25.893 --> 10:27.527
Of what?

10:27.560 --> 10:29.162
Of when he died.

10:29.196 --> 10:31.699
Santino died
in the summer.

10:31.732 --> 10:33.100
He died in June.

10:33.133 --> 10:35.035
No, he died now,
in December.

10:35.068 --> 10:38.538
I know when
my brother died.

10:38.571 --> 10:41.775
This isn't the anniversary
of when Santino died?

10:41.809 --> 10:43.143
No.

10:43.176 --> 10:45.713
Did he tell you it was?

10:45.746 --> 10:47.314
[ Sighs ]

10:47.347 --> 10:48.782
Never mind.

10:48.816 --> 10:52.352
I'm obviously confused.

10:52.385 --> 10:55.022
But he's camping
for some reason.

10:57.691 --> 10:59.059
Jacob:
Why are you going camping?

10:59.092 --> 11:00.728
Letty: What do you mean?
I'm just going.

11:00.761 --> 11:01.962
Why don't I get to go?

11:01.995 --> 11:03.396
Look, we'll go
another time.

11:03.430 --> 11:06.066
Right now you get to
hang out with Apple.

11:06.099 --> 11:06.967
Yeah.

11:07.000 --> 11:09.469
[ Doorbell rings ]

11:09.502 --> 11:12.639
Hey!
Hey!

11:12.672 --> 11:13.907
Aw!

11:13.941 --> 11:15.208
Hi, Michael.

11:15.242 --> 11:17.377
I hear you have
an interview on Monday.

11:17.410 --> 11:18.578
What do you say?

11:18.611 --> 11:19.847
Thank you.

11:19.880 --> 11:21.314
Thank you
for letting him stay over.

11:21.348 --> 11:23.016
Oh, of course.
Are you, me, and Apple

11:23.050 --> 11:24.752
gonna have a good time
tonight or what?

11:24.785 --> 11:26.419
Okay.

11:26.453 --> 11:28.688
Seriously, Carin, thank you
for getting him the interview.

11:28.722 --> 11:30.357
After that whole thing
with your husband, I --

11:30.390 --> 11:32.592
Oh, don't worry about Eric --
seriously.

11:32.625 --> 11:34.061
Okay.
I got to go.

11:34.094 --> 11:35.362
Where are you going
again?

11:35.395 --> 11:37.097
Just a quick camping thing
with Emile.

11:37.130 --> 11:38.498
Where? The state park?

11:38.531 --> 11:39.699
Yeah.

11:39.733 --> 11:41.869
Isn't that kind of gross?
Yeah.

11:41.902 --> 11:43.703
See you tomorrow.
Thank you!

11:43.737 --> 11:46.339
Bye!

11:46.373 --> 11:48.441
**

11:48.475 --> 11:52.279
* I meditate on the end of days
till I get it straight *

11:52.312 --> 11:55.115
* Die every day, die every day

11:55.148 --> 12:00.087
* We come and die every day,
die every day *

12:00.120 --> 12:03.924
* Just fly every day,
fly every day *

12:03.957 --> 12:05.458
* Ohh

12:05.492 --> 12:08.728
Pull that back out of the ground
so I can murder you with it.

12:08.762 --> 12:11.464
* Die every day

12:15.402 --> 12:16.569
You can't stay.

12:16.603 --> 12:19.106
Why are you really here?
I told you.

12:19.139 --> 12:21.308
This isn't when
Santino died.

12:21.341 --> 12:23.143
I know when
my brother died.

12:23.176 --> 12:25.145
So does your sister,
apparently.

12:25.178 --> 12:27.414
What?
You talked to Ava?

12:27.447 --> 12:29.582
Yeah.
She called me today.

12:29.616 --> 12:31.384
She wanted to talk
about you --

12:31.418 --> 12:33.253
because knowing you
is so annoying,

12:33.286 --> 12:34.822
people have to find
other people

12:34.855 --> 12:36.890
who understand
how annoying it is

12:36.924 --> 12:39.126
to talk to about it.

12:39.159 --> 12:44.464
And she told me that Santino
died in the summer.

12:44.497 --> 12:46.099
She meant our summer.

12:46.133 --> 12:47.467
What?

12:47.500 --> 12:51.104
Argentinian summer --
It's during American winter.

12:51.138 --> 12:52.505
There are two summers.

12:52.539 --> 12:56.143
It is different when you're
south of the equator.

12:56.176 --> 12:59.112
She said June.

12:59.146 --> 13:00.680
Fine, it was June.

13:00.713 --> 13:02.816
Why didn't you tell me
you talked to her?

13:02.850 --> 13:04.784
Are you really
giving me shit right now?

13:04.818 --> 13:06.619
I didn't tell you
because I thought

13:06.653 --> 13:08.521
you were on some
Argentinian-style walkabout

13:08.555 --> 13:09.957
mourning your dead brother.

13:09.990 --> 13:11.791
Do you know how insane
that is to lie about?

13:11.825 --> 13:13.093
You are seriously damaged.

13:13.126 --> 13:15.195
You lie about everything.

13:15.228 --> 13:17.197
Hold this.

13:17.230 --> 13:18.531
Where did you
get this tent?

13:18.565 --> 13:21.768
Craigslist.

13:21.801 --> 13:23.303
Just tell me
why you're here --

13:23.336 --> 13:24.704
right now.

13:24.737 --> 13:27.474
Are you here for work?

13:27.507 --> 13:29.376
[ Sighs ] Yes.

13:29.409 --> 13:31.945
I knew it. I knew it.

13:31.979 --> 13:34.147
You've been telling me
what a fucked-up junkie I am

13:34.181 --> 13:36.616
since we met, but you're the one
with the problem.

13:36.649 --> 13:38.485
That's why you didn't want
Jacob and me to come.

13:38.518 --> 13:41.221
In case you don't remember,
you're the one who came back.

13:41.254 --> 13:42.655
You came back to us,

13:42.689 --> 13:45.692
showed up at my mom's house --
you chose that.

13:45.725 --> 13:47.961
If you didn't want this with us,
then why did you do that?

13:47.995 --> 13:49.329
Just to screw it up
for me?

13:49.362 --> 13:50.830
Screw it up?

13:50.864 --> 13:53.733
I am fixing it for you right
now. That is what I'm doing.

13:53.766 --> 13:55.568
Jacob needs money
for school,

13:55.602 --> 13:57.504
so I'm here
getting money for school.

13:57.537 --> 14:00.673
I can't be there for my sister,
I can't be there for my nieces,

14:00.707 --> 14:02.675
I have no idea
what happened to Silk,

14:02.709 --> 14:04.344
but Jacob...that is
something I can fix

14:04.377 --> 14:05.678
for someone I love.

14:05.712 --> 14:07.547
I told you I have
that money covered.

14:07.580 --> 14:08.916
I'm getting it tomorrow.

14:08.949 --> 14:09.917
From where?

14:09.950 --> 14:12.385
Other people's
hotel rooms, huh?

14:12.419 --> 14:13.653
And then you go to prison.

14:13.686 --> 14:14.854
Talk about screwing it up.

14:14.888 --> 14:16.356
Talk about
screwing Jacob's life up.

14:16.389 --> 14:18.091
No.
I will get the money.

14:18.125 --> 14:20.260
By murdering somebody?
Well, that is what I do.

14:20.293 --> 14:23.530
And since I met you, I haven't
had one job go smoothly.

14:23.563 --> 14:25.698
So, please...

14:25.732 --> 14:27.935
leave me alone to do it.

14:29.636 --> 14:35.008
If it makes you feel any better,
he raped a girl.

14:35.042 --> 14:36.676
What?

14:36.709 --> 14:39.112
The person I'm here to kill.

14:39.146 --> 14:41.949
So he's just conveniently
a rapist,

14:41.982 --> 14:44.451
the worst thing
a person can be?

14:44.484 --> 14:47.854
The last time you did this, it
was someone trying to kill you.

14:47.887 --> 14:49.522
And then Silk was just
coincidentally murdered

14:49.556 --> 14:50.623
that same night.

14:50.657 --> 14:52.025
Thank you
for reminding me.

14:52.059 --> 14:53.393
How do you know
this isn't another setup?

14:53.426 --> 14:54.894
Because that was
three days ago,

14:54.928 --> 14:57.030
and this posting was up
for seven days.

14:57.064 --> 14:58.065
I'm sure it was.

14:58.098 --> 15:00.767
How many hitmen
want to go camping?

15:00.800 --> 15:02.235
I guess just one.

15:02.269 --> 15:04.604
[ Vehicles approaching ]

15:04.637 --> 15:07.474
He's here.

15:07.507 --> 15:16.783
**

15:16.816 --> 15:18.785
[ Indistinct talking ]

15:19.919 --> 15:23.256
It's the guy
in the brown jacket.

15:23.290 --> 15:24.624
[ Indistinct talking continues ]

15:24.657 --> 15:26.593
His name is Bryce.

15:26.626 --> 15:29.096
Of course his name
is Bryce.

15:29.129 --> 15:30.597
[ Chair rattles ]

15:30.630 --> 15:31.898
You should go now.

15:31.931 --> 15:34.434
So should you.
Let's go.

15:34.467 --> 15:35.468
[ Sighs ]

15:35.502 --> 15:37.504
I am camping.

15:37.537 --> 15:40.207
[ Bag unzips ]
Then I'm camping, too.

15:45.712 --> 15:47.447
What do you have to eat?

15:47.480 --> 15:48.848
You said this was gross.

15:48.881 --> 15:51.918
It is, but I'm staying here
and pretending it's not

15:51.951 --> 15:54.487
so I can stop you
from killing someone --

15:54.521 --> 15:55.955
just like
when we first met.

15:55.989 --> 16:01.294
Well, I still killed
that person in the end, so...

16:01.328 --> 16:04.697
Bees? What is this?

16:04.731 --> 16:06.533
Tell me what that was.
No.

16:06.566 --> 16:09.269
Tell me.

